    "comment": "Rationale: Fig. 5 SAPAP3 is enriched in PSD fractions\nLiteral: \"We found that SAPAP1, -3, and -4 were all highly enriched in PSD fractions.\"\n\nFig. 8 SAPAP3 is expressed at neuronal cholinergic synapses\nLiteral \"SAPAP 3 is highly enriched at synapses in the submandibular ganglion, as demonstrated by simultaneously staining the sections for the presynaptic marker protein synaptophysin (Fig. 8B,D,F).\n\nFig 11 SAPAP3 proteins colocalize with PSD-95.\nLiteral \"SAPAP1, -3, and -4 all showed extensive colocalization with PSD-95 (Fig. 11), implying, as expected, that SAPAP1, -3, and -4 were located at glutamatergic synapses in the spinal cord.. Experimental description: PSD preparation\nLiteral \"The PSD fraction of whole mouse brain was prepared as described\nFluorescent immunohistochemistry\nLiteral \"P21-P28 mice were deeply anesthetized with halothane and perfused transcardially with lactated Ringer's solution.",
